","slug":"ebola","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/tag\/ebola\/"},"tags":"airborne Ebola|ebola|Ebola in Liberia|Infectious Disease|Liberia","hero":{"class":"landscape","thumbnail":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/01\/128587211.jpg?w=100&h=100&crop=1","src":{"small":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/01\/128587211.jpg?w=280","small_2x":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/01\/128587211.jpg?w=560","large":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/01\/128587211.jpg?w=550","large_2x":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/01\/128587211.jpg?w=1100"},"credit":"SCOTT CAMAZINE&mdash;Getty Images\/Photo Researchers RM","caption":"At one time in 2014, Liberia experienced the fastest growing number of Ebola cases","alt":"128587211","providers":[],"masonry":{"small_width":300,"small_height":236,"large_width":625,"large_height":493}},"id":3665546,"encoded_url":"http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3665546%2Febola-may-end-2015-liberia%2F","encoded_shortlink":"http%3A%2F%2Fti.me%2F1u1ZX9l","encoded_title":"Ebola+Epidemic+May+End+by+June+2015+In+Liberia","twitter_text":"Ebola%20epidemic%20may%20end%20by%20June%202015%20in%20Liberia","twitter_via":"TIMEHealth","subjects":[null],"ads":{"neg":"false","post_title":"Ebola Epidemic May End by June 2015 In Liberia"},"Partner_Module":{"partner":"Select","post_title":"Ebola Epidemic May End by June 2015 In Liberia"},"email_title":"Ebola%20Epidemic%20May%20End%20by%20June%202015%20In%20Liberia%20%7C%20TIME","email_body":"Ebola%20Epidemic%20May%20End%20by%20June%202015%20In%20Liberia%0A%0AThat%E2%80%99s%20only%20if%20current%20hospitalization%20rates%20continue%2C%20say%20researchers%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3665546%2Febola-may-end-2015-liberia%2F","omniture":{"modules":"rr-outbrain|rr-ad|rr-share"},"outbrain":{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3665546\/ebola-may-end-2015-liberia\/","widget_id":"AR_6"},"article_tile_thumbnail":"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/01\/128587211.jpg?w=74&h=74&crop=1"},{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3658054\/ebola-drug-clinical-trial\/","shortlink":"http:\/\/ti.me\/1Dy8D7q","title":"Clinical Trial for Ebola Drug Starts in Liberia","friendly_title":"Clinical Trial for Ebola Drug Starts in Liberia","post_type":"post","available":true,"time_article":true,"comments_allowed":true,"short_title":"Clinical Trial for Ebola Drug Starts in Liberia","excerpt":"University of Oxford researchers are offering patients in Liberia a new drug for Ebola","format":"brief","time":{"pretty":"Jan. 7, 2015","published":"2015-01-07 13:32:02","updated":"2015-01-07 18:32:02","minute":"1:32 pm","short":"1\/7"},"authors":[{"id":207020909,"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/author\/alexandra-sifferlin\/","name":"Alexandra Sifferlin","bio":"Alexandra Sifferlin is a writer for TIME. She covers public health issues including infectious and chronic disease, big ideas in medicine, and breaking news.","short_bio":"","types":[],"twitter":"acsifferlin","twitter_url":"https:\/\/twitter.com\/acsifferlin","gplus":"110376986433078721859","fb":"","email":"","thumbnail":"http:\/\/i1.wp.com\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/01\/mg_1589.jpg?crop=441px%2C168px%2C2423px%2C2422px&resize=100%2C100","contributor":false,"search_link":false}],"content":"<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-related\" data-name=\"rr-related\"><div class=\"read-more-inline related\"><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3652455\/ebola-2015-un\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-brief data-event=\"rr-related\"><img src=\"https:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/10\/ebola-caregiver-person-of-the-year.jpg?w=268&#038;h=268&#038;crop=1\" alt=\"Red Cross workers carry away the body of a person suspected of dying from the Ebola virus, in the Monrovia, Liberia on Oct. 4, 2014.\" title=\"Red Cross workers carry away the body of a person suspected of dying from the Ebola virus in Monrovia, Liberia on Oct. 4, 2014. \"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h\">More<\/h6><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\">U.N. Official Says Ebola Can Be Beat in 2015<\/h3><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3651069\/ebola-survivor-rick-sacra-returning-liberia\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article data-event=\"rr-related\"><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\">Ebola Survivor Rick Sacra: Why I\u2019m Going Back to Liberia in the New Year<\/h3><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3650999\/ebola-guinea-bats\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article data-event=\"rr-related\"><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\">Here&#8217;s Where Scientists Believe the Ebola Epidemic Started<\/h3><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>Scientists have started testing an experimental drug for Ebola in a Liberian hospital.<\/p>\n<p>University of Oxford researchers have launched a trial of the drug, brincidofovir, in Doctors Without Borders&#8217; Ebola center in Monrovia. The drug has previously been used to treat patients with Ebola in the United States, like <a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.com\/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=2&amp;ved=0CCUQFjAB&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3475718%2Fdallas-ebola-experimental-drug%2F&amp;ei=F3itVMXELIXHsQS3gILICA&amp;usg=AFQjCNHtzwMhss-U6jE3slnEOH60Xhdv7A&amp;sig2=ku0BOFV-cLyGpr9TgDuB-A&amp;bvm=bv.83134100,d.cWc&amp;cad=rja\" target=\"_blank\">Thomas Eric Duncan<\/a>, NBC cameraman <a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3530334\/ebola-ashoka-mukpo-nbc-freelance-cameraman\/\" target=\"_blank\">Ashoka Mukpo<\/a>, and <a href=\"http:\/\/www.nydailynews.com\/life-style\/health\/dr-craig-spencer-experimental-anti-viral-drug-brincidofovir-fight-ebola-officials-article-1.1986996\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Craig Spencer<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>When patients at the unit are informed they have Ebola, they will be offered the opportunity to participate in the trial. Patients who volunteer will be given two weeks of brincidofovir. The researchers estimate there will be about 140 participants. &#8220;Typically it takes over 18 months to start a trial. Here we have done it in less than four months,&#8221; Trudie Lang, an Oxford University professor, said <a href=\"http:\/\/www.ox.ac.uk\/news\/2015-01-07-trial-potential-treatment-ebola-begins-liberia\" target=\"_blank\">in a statement<\/a>. &#8220;Everyone has pulled together to make it happen&mdash;a Herculean effort by all those involved.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><strong>MORE: <\/strong><a title=\"TIME Person of the Year: Ebola Fighters\" href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/poy\" target=\"_blank\">TIME Person of the Year, the Ebola Fighters<\/a><\/p>\n<p>The drug, which was originally developed for other viruses, has shown promise fighting the Ebola virus in test-tubes, but it&#8217;s nearly impossible to know whether the drug has been of any use in the small number of patients who have tried it.<\/p>\n<p>Brincidofovir is manufactured by the pharmaceutical company Chimerix in Durham, N.C. The trial is funded by the biomedical research foundation, the Wellcome Trust.<\/p><div class=\"content-ad\" id=\"content-ad-3658054\"><\/div>\n<p>To date, 20,712 people have been infected with Ebola during the current outbreak and 8,220 have died.<\/p>\n\t\t\t<form id=\"wpcom-iframe-form-40bd30ac347dee4d0f4e23c8bb376284-54cc19b36ca0d\" target=\"wpcom-iframe-40bd30ac347dee4d0f4e23c8bb376284-54cc19b36ca0d\" method=\"post\" action=\"\/\/wpcomwidgets.com\/?wpcom_origin=https%3A%2F%2Ftimedotcom.wordpress.com\" style=\"display: none\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"frameborder\" value=\"0\" \/>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"scrolling\" value=\"no\" \/>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"resize\" value=\"0\" \/>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"replace_attributes\" value=\"1\" \/>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"fallback\" value=\"&lt;p class=&quot;protected-embed-fallback&quot;&gt;This embed is invalid&lt;\/p&gt;\" \/>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"class\" value=\"\" \/>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"width\" value=\"100%\" \/>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" nam